title: Arizona Democrat Ruben Gallego announces Senate bid in challenge to Kyrsten Sinema
description: Democratic Rep. Ruben Gallego of Arizona on Monday announced his campaign for US Senate, setting up a potential 2024 clash with Sen. Kyrsten Sinema, who recently switched her party affiliation from Democrat to independent.
author: Kate Sullivan, Kyung Lah

title: Utah governor signs major education funding bill, becoming third state to enshrine school choice into law
description: Utah Gov. Spencer Cox on Sunday signed a major school choice bill on Sunday, giving parents more options for their children’s education.
author: Joshua Nelson

title: Democratic Arizona Gov. Katie Hobbs defends decision to keep busing migrants out of state
description: Democratic Arizona Gov. Katie Hobbs is defending her decision to keep in place her predecessor's program to bus migrants out of the state.
author: Bradford Betz

title: Iowa just latest government-school domino to fall, and there's nothing teachers' unions can do about it
description: The Republican-controlled Iowa Legislature passed an expansive school choice proposal and Gov. Kim Reynolds signed the bill Tuesday.
author: Corey DeAngelis

title: Iowa Gov Kim Reynolds signs historic school choice bill: 'We will fund students not systems'
description: Iowa Gov. Kim Reynolds signed the Students First Act on Tuesday, becoming the second state to pass a school choice measure that expands to every student in the state.
author: Joshua Q. Nelson | Fox News

title: Controversy as NYPD caught filming attendees exiting a Drake concert
description: The New York City Police Department is under fire for recording attendees at a Drake concert without their consent, although the department insists the video is for social media use only.
author: Associated Press

title: Arizona GOP bows to election denialism in bid for unity
description: Jeff DeWit, a former state treasurer and Trump campaign aide, wooed prominent election deniers to stave off far-right challenge
author: Yvonne Wingett Sanchez

title: Rep. Ruben Gallego Announces Bid for Kyrsten Sinema’s Arizona Senate Seat
description: Ruben Gallego, a liberal firebrand, announced Monday he'll challenge independent U.S. Sen. Kyrsten Sinema in 2024.
author: JONATHAN J. COOPER / AP

title: Dying at work: How Arizona fails to protect workers on the job
description: Under former Gov. Doug Ducey, Arizona workplace safety inspections dwindled and fines to companies decreased, all while injuries and deaths rose.
author: Anne Ryman and Justin Price
